inn1.comm: on target first up, pitches it on a good length just fractionally outside off, Strauss covers it well, presenting the full face

shot off the track, hit a crack on the pitch that, short of a good length just marginally outside off stump, surprises Strauss as it kicks off, takes the outside edge, a very thin one, and McCullum makes no mistake
angling in towards middle, tries to play it forward, gets a thick inside edge down to fine leg for a single
pushed it fuller, in line with middle, defended with a still head back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, prods it towards cover on the front foot
shortish on leg stump, worked down to midwicket
starts well, bowled on a good length outside off, gets a hint of movement away from the batsman, left alone to the keeper
darted back in, bowled at 136kmph, not much foot movement from Shah who tries to guide it down to third man but is almost done in by the swing back in
good carry through to McCullum who takes it in front of his face, in the channel outside off, Shah watches it through
short and wide, a hint of inward movement, Shah restrains himself from playing the cut
back of a length on middle, turned away through square leg, well wide of fine leg, there's an easy three on offer but Shah's not for it
short of a good length on middle, gets back and dabs it into the leg side
eased it through point and cover, nicely timed, short and wide, just punched it from the crease
back of a length outside off, too wide, left alone
slightly short just outside off, gets back, stands tall and taps it to cover
short of a good length on middle, gets on the back foot and turns it just wide of midwicket for a quick single
shortish outside off again, jabs it to cover off the back foot
shaping away from the right hander, hitting the right length just outside off, moved away, left it alone safely through to the keeper
back of a length on middle, kept a little low this time, uneven bounce here, defended comfortably off the back foot
bowled at 138.4 kmph, darted back in just a touch from a good length outside off, Denly judged it well,, shouldering arms at the right time
poor stuff from Ross Taylor in the slips, kicked back in to rap Denly on the thighs and it deflected towards first slip where Taylor made a mess of it to concede a couple of runs
gets forward and defends it solidly to cover, moved back in from a good length outside off
timber! Kept low, came back in and Denly failed to get his bat down in time, seamed in and moved inwards off the pitch as well to knock back the off stump
short on middle, Collingwood shuffles a hint and nudges it down to fine leg for a single to keep strike
too short, too wide, Collingwood cracks it between extra cover and mid-off for a couple of runs
much better, tempting length, trying to induce him into playing the drive, Collingwood has nothing to do with it
overpitched outside off, driven through the line to mid-off
back of a length, bowled at 131.6kmph, just outside off, Collingwood rocks back and taps it down to cover
seaming away just a fraction, Collingwood is well behind it and knocks it down to midwicket
kept really low, he was lucky that didn't pitch in line, just outside off and shot through to the keeper under the bat
got him! Awkward short from Shah, bowled it full outside off, got it to move away, Shah moved across and tried to flick it over square leg, got a thick edge straight to McCullum
off the mark, pushes it back past Bond, wide of a diving mid-on for a single
bowled on a good length outside off, tapped cautiously towards cover
good bounce this time, tempting line outside off, Collingwood isn't going for it
back of a length outside off, just a hint of movement back in, left alone again
unplayable! Almost identical to the delivery that proved Strauss's undoing, except that it was a little wider and got a little more bounce, Collingwood got a shock, was lucky he didn't nick it
bowled on a good length outside off, appears to hold its line, left through to the keeper
shout for lbw, short of a good length on the off and nips back in to strike Morgan on the pads as he tries to play it on the leg side, would have gone over the stumps
fullish on the off, worked down to midwicket from the crease
edged and short, cut back in sharply and almost did him in with the bounce, Morgan was playing forward, took his bottom hand off at the right time and it dropped short of the diving keeper
angling it in towards middle, tickled behind square for a couple of runs
fuller on the off stump, defended uneasily towards extra cover off the front foot
pushed off the front foot in the direction over
a slight shuffle from Collingwood even before it's delivered, good length on the off, tapped down towards midwicket
short and wide, chops it down towards cover, didn't time that well, there was a chance to relieve some pressure
cut back in from a good length outside off, moves all the way back and knocks it on the off side

Memories of that game against Sri Lanka, capitalised on the short one this time, got into position early and smashed him over square leg for six, did the same in that Man-of-the-Match effort against Malinga
kept low this time, tried to punch it wide of the covers but it had zipped through him
angling it just outside off, moves across and defends it to point
teasing him this time, bowled it much closer to the stumps and got it to nip away as Morgan prodded at it, was beaten
coming back in this time, gets front and across and defends it with a closed face back to the bowler
pushed it fuller, on a driving length outside off, drives it gently to extra cover
beaten by the inswinger, hitting the right areas outside off and Morgan can't gauge the extent of the movement, just presents his bat and makes no contact
short of a length outside off, tries to guide it wide of point but is unable to do, a diving save prevents a single

run-out attempt, Guptill could have done better, short outside off, punched it just wide of Guptill at extra cover and set off, there wasn't a single on offer there, had he scored a direct hit, Collingwood was gone
short of a good length outside off, hitting the pitch hard, left alone
excellent carry through to McCullum who has to leap to snap that good length delivery
back of a length, again outside off, Morgan lets it through
pushed it fuller, played it gently down to extra cover off the front foot
Morgan shouldered arms and turned back immediately with surprise, for it didn't bounce as much as he expected, seen those reactions quite a few times today
shout for lbw, nipped back in to strike Collingwood on the pads, had shuffled and was playing off the back foot, what saved him there was the inside edge
fullish outside off, gets forward, opens the face and knocks it down to point
short of a good length on the off stump, tries to force it off the back foot through the covers, mistimes it back to the bowler
short, bowled at 132.1 kmph, pushed off the back foot to extra cover
improvisation from Collingwood, overpitched on the off stump, just chips it over the in-field, over the bowler's head and the two fielders in the V for a much-needed boundary

appeal, banged in short outside off, left alone, Collingwood walks down the pitch, McCullum throws down the stumps at the striker's end, the umpires are consulting, had the umpire Harper called over by the time the batsman walked down? Daryl Harper talks to Vettori, who chats with his team-mates to come up with a decision. The third umpire has given it out, but there are still discussions happening out in the middle. Collingwood has a word with Vettori, and the New Zealand captain's decided to withdraw the appeal and allowed Collingwood to continue.
kept low and he got the inside edge as he tried to push it off the back foot
banged in short outside off, left alone to the keeper
fuller outside off, moving away from the left-hander, left alone to the keeper
short of a good length outside off, got it to dart away from Morgan who pushed at it from the crease and was beaten
fullish outside off, leaving Morgan and he lets it through
short of a good length outside off, moving away a hint, moves across and taps it to cover
hurled it short on middle, Collingwood moved back and dropped it on the leg side, hit high on the bat and lobbed up for just a bit
angling it in towards middle at 129.5 kmph, defended towards cover
short of a good length outside off, guided it down to third man for a single
driving  length and Morgan is sucked in, goes for it and is beaten by the movement
short of a good length on middle, worked away off the back foot through square leg for a single
short and wide, taps it down, playing slightly away from his body, towards cover
opportunity gifted and Morgan cashes in, short and wide and he cuts it hard through cover and point for a boundary
shortish outside off, needs to get it fuller, played down to point off the back foot
driven hard but straight to extra cover, not much movement so far for Franklin
short of a good length outside off, a touch too wide, left alone to the keeper
pushed it on a good length and got it to move away prodigiously, quite a contrast to Franklin in the previous over, left alone
rare loss in concentration from Collingwood, short of a good length outside off, tried to drive it hard off the back foot through cover, away from his body, and was beaten
straying on the pads and some appalling fielding from Guptill at square leg concedes two more, through square leg
full on the off and moved away, Collingwood pushed through the line and got a thick edge as it moved away, no gully in place, he gets a single to third man
in the slot on leg stump, driving length, drilled into the ground but straight to mid-on
banged in short outside off, in the zone for Collingwood who pulls it disdainfully over midwicket for a boundary
bowled full outside off, pushed through to mid-on
bowled on a good length outside off, holds its line, Collingwood lets it go
back of a length on the off, defended down towards cover
fullish outside off, gets him to drive but he's not able to get it to move around, pushed through to mid-off
they've targeted Franklin, short on middle, poor length to Collingwood, rocks back and pulls it hard over the long-leg boundary for a big six
in the channel outside off, getting some good carry through to the keeper
fullish outside off, a little too wide sho Morgan isn't tempted to play at it
pitched it up on the off stump, driven through to mid-off
back of a length this time, maintaining that line outside off, left alone
fullish outside off, pushed through hard wide of cover into the deep for a couple of runs
bowled on a good length outside off, held its line and Collingwood let it through
pitched up outside off, steered down to cover from the crease, had to reach for that a bit
short of a good length on the off, moves across and defends it into the leg side
hurls it just outside off this time, defended solidly down to cover

Collingwood almost did a Shah there, charged down the track to a fullish delivery outside off, but there wasn't a flourish there, just tried to drive it past midwicket, got a thick edge down to third man
short and wide, tries to chop it past point but makes no contact
short on middle, worked down through square leg for a single

gone! Butler strikes! Short outside off, got some extra bounce there, went for the cut, got a thick edge and McCullum, trying to collect it over his head, fumbled it and it lobbed up behind him, sharp reaction from Taylor at first slip who dived to his right to complete the catch
struck on the glove, shot off the pitch after landing on middle, nipped back in, he took his bottom hand off at the right time, but that must hurt, taking the pain is  Bopara
defended into the leg side off the front foot
a rare extra from New Zealand, Butler slides that down the leg side
short of a length outside off, Bopara plays it well, takes the bottom-hand off and guides it down to third man, played it really late
shortish on middle, rocks back and turns it down to midwicket
fullish on the off, covers it well by getting to the pitch and defending it towards cover
full outside off, leaving the right hander, Bopara leaves it be
almost chipped it straight to Bond, moving in towards middle, pushed it uppishly but fell safe, short of Bond running in from mid-on
hurls it on a good length outside off, holds its line this time, left alone
pitched up and Collingwood takes full toll, launching Franklin out of the ground over long-on, the slower one that, Collingwood spotted it
moves across and defends it with bat close to pad on the leg side
hurling it down the leg side again, McCullum keeps well, diving to his left
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot into the leg side
oversteps, freehit time, Butler losing it slightly by conceding these extras, defended into the off side
cashes in, short outside off, makes way and smacks it over mid-on for a couple of bounces over the ropes
back of a length outside off, gets a thick edge wide of a diving second slip down to third man for a couple
a touch too straight, nudged away into the leg side for a single
Collingwood senses another six with that short one but he was little on it, tried to pull it hard but mistimed it behind square for just a single
bowled full outside off, driven through to extra cover
how did that miss? Almost rolled down the pitch after it hit the pitch, Collingwood was lucky that didn't pitch in line with the stumps, there was no way anyone could have played that
shortish outside off, defended towards point
important runs, these extras, another one down the leg side
full on middle, driven down to deep midwicket for a single
almost had him there! Short outside off, Bopara goes for the cut, gets a thick edge wide of a diving Taylor down to third man, lucky escape there
bowled at 120.2 kmph, too wide outside off, another extra run
misfield in the deep, New Zealand are losing their guard slightly, turned away down to fine leg, a fumble allows them to come back for the second
short of a length outside off, chopped down into the deep on the off side for a single
back of a length on middle, defended on the pitch
cutting it in, Bopara prods at that good length delivery and plays inside the line, is beaten
pitched it up outside off, tried to drive it through to mid-off, the bat turned in his hand and it rolled down to midwicket
seaming away, Bopara was left playing away from his body there and was promptly beaten
shortish on the off stump, bowled at 138.1 kmph, defended from the crease down towards point
back of a length on the off, drops it down into the leg side, sets off for a single but it's not there, is rightly sent back
slower one bowled short outside off, pulled down to deep midwicket for a single
bowled full on middle, defended with a straight bat down towards mid-on
slower one bowled full on leg stump, tickled through square leg for a single
back of a length on middle, turned down to midwicket
full outside off, holds its line, Collingwood doesn't play at it

Excellent catch by Taylor! Short outside off, went for the pull, it appeared it came on to him a little too quickly, mistimed it, hit him high on the bat but it seemed as though it would just about clear midwicket, but Taylor leapt with his outstretched right hand, timing his jump to perfection and snapping it out of thin air to end Collingwood's fighting knock
bowled on a good length outside off, defended into the leg side
short of a good length on the off, defended solidly off the back foot, oversteps again, another freehit
full and wide, he makes room and slices it over point for a boundary, Butler's bled extras
a wide now, down the leg side, McCullum tries to salvage something out of a useless appeal, the umpire's having none of it
banged in short outside off, guided down to point from the crease
bowled on a good length outside off, gets forward and defends it down to mid-off
short of a good length outside off, punched down to cover off the back foot
shortish outside off, military medium stuff, 118 kmph, pushed to point
bowled full on the off, driven down to mid-off
pushed off the front foot to midwicket
banged in short, Wright is on to it quickly, rocking back and pulling it hard through midwicket for a boundary
bowled on a good length outside off, defended to cover

edged and gone! Probing line just a fraction outside off and just a hint of away movement with some extra bounce, a lethal combination, Wright plays at it, is surprised by the bounce and nicks it straight to the keeper
short on middle, worked away through square leg for two more
back of a length on the off, punched down to extra cover
back of a length outside off, chopped down towards point, well fielded by Taylor there who dived to his left
back of a length on middle, rocks back and dabs it towards cover
full on the off, pushed through to deep cover for a single
short and wide, goes for the cut, gets an underedge down to the keeper
round the wicket and hurls it down the leg side, one more extra run

caught and bowled! England continue to slide, bowled on a good length on middle, hit the pitch hard as well as the bat, Broad tried to defend it onto the pitch with hard hands, it struck him high on the bat and lobbed up in front of Elliott who bent low and took it clean on his follow-through
lands on a good length on leg stump, Swann just tries to fend it away, goes uppish through square leg
short and wide, cracked off the back foot wide of deep cover for a couple of runs
slower one bowled short outside off, tapped down to point
beaten! Angling it in towards off and getting it to move off the pitch, Bopara was squared up and had no answer to that one
bowled on a good length outside off, moves away, left alone to the keeper
back of a length on middle, defended into the leg side wide of the bowler
bowled full outside off, held its line, Swann played inside the line to that one, made no contact
bowled at 140.8kmph, zips through the keeper as Swann leaves it alone
pushed away from his body back to the bowler, full and fast
the offcutter, bowled at 138 kmph, guided down to third man for a single
banged in short on middle, swipes it to deep square leg for a single
slower one bowled short outside off, cut down to sweeper cover for a single
lands on a length on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
aggression from Swann, shortish outside off, thwacked over extra cover into the deep for a couple of runs
spotted the slower one bowled at 91 kmph, defended it watchfully back to the bowler
bowled fullish outside off, pushed down to sweeper cover for a single
short of a good length on the off, tapped down towards point
back of a length, pushed off the back foot towards cover
full and wide and Swann has dispatched it, creamed it past extra cover to the ropes, raced away
fell just short, bowled short outside off, the slower one, Swann tried to bunt that over cover, mistimed it, it fell inches short of a charging Vettori from mid-off
back of a length outside off, cut down to point
pushed off the back foot wide of cover for a quick single, Guptill it was again, a safe bet for a single this innings
pushed off the back foot to cover

Elliott takes four! Bangs it in short again, it's fetched him wickets today, Swann goes for the pull, again a little late into the shot, gets the top edge and McCullum waits endlessly for the law of gravity to take effect and watches it into his palms
fullish on middle, defended into the leg side towards midwicket
bowled full outside off, left alone to the keeper, round the wicket to the left-hander
driving length outside off, shoulders arms to that one
bowled full at 140.7 kmph on middle, turned down to deep midwicket for a single
short of a good length on middle, 143.9 kmph, dabbed down to midwicket
short outside off, tries to play at it initially but then withdraws, gets a thick edge wide of Elliott at second slip, he dives to his left and saves a couple of runs
played it down deliberately this time, down to third man
the offcutter, bowled at 127.8 kmph, tapped into the leg side in front of midwicket
banged in short on middle, pulled it with restraint over square leg for a couple of runs, it means Sidebottom's on strike in the next over
bowled full on the pads, tried to glance it down, was rapped on the pads, no run there
banged in short on leg stump, tries to whip it fine, gets it behind square for a single
short on leg stump, turned down to fine leg, thinks of a second but no chance
bowled on a good length on the off, pushed down to mid-off
pushed off the back foot towards cover
full and wide down the leg side, one more to this total
slower one bowled short outside off, went at it hard off the back foot, but it was  bowled slower and kept low, no contact made
bowled full outside off, tries to drive it through the line, gets a thick outside edge to point
slower one bowled short on the off, gets on the back foot and taps it wide of second slip
bowled full on middle at 138.9 kmph, driven down to mid-on
short of a good length on the off, gets behind it nicely and defends it back to the bowler
slower one bowled short outside off, chops it down to point, no single there

plumb! Kept low, the pitch is still doing things, bowled on a good length on middle and didn't rise up one bit, struck Bopara extremely low on the pads as he went across to work it into the leg side, no way he was going to get down to playing that one, England are nine down, was struck in line with middle and leg

appeal for a catch, bowled short down the leg side, Sidebottom tries to help it on its way down to fine leg, McCullum went up, it may have flicked his shirt on the way, Sidebottom shook his head immediately, tough to tell
pushed off the front foot to cover
short outside off, cut down to third man for a single
stopped on him a little there, he was through with his shot, lobbed up over extra cover, fell safe and he took a single
bowled full and slow on middle, wristily turned away through square leg for a couple more
short of a good length outside off, tries to punch it off the back foot, gets an inside edge onto his thighs
bowled full on the off, moves back, opens the face and plays it to point
short of a good length on the off, punched down to deep cover for a single
tries to fend it through square leg, was struck high on the pads, they squeeze a leg bye
kept low again, for the umpteenth time, just outside off and zipped under his bat, you can't play at those
in the blockhole on middle, dug out towards mid-off
pushed firmly off the back foot but straight to extra cover
short of a length outside off, tries to force it hard off the back foot, is nowhere near it
much fuller, goes for the drive, moved away just a hint off the pitch and beat the outside edge
short of a good length on the off, pushed down towards mid-off
bowled full outside off, driven into the ground straight to Guptill at extra cover
a touch fullish outside off, cracked down to deep point for a single
shortish on middle, pushes through the line, gets a thick edge well short of Taylor at first slip
round the wicket and shortish on middle, tries to push it hard past midwicket, gets an inside edge onto the pads
short outside off, tries to thump it through the covers, limited footwork there, doesn't connect
struck well, short on middle, rocks back and pulls it over square leg for a one bounce four

more, short on leg stump, worked away off the hips behind square, fine leg takes a while to run across and cut that off, it appears Mills has just dragged it back in, but it's too tough to tell, replays confirm it's a boundary
full outside off, driven back to the bowler and Butler, in frustration, pretends to hurl it back down the pitch
short on the off, punched off the back foot to Guptill at cover
short and wide, slashes hard, is nowhere near it
short on the off, pushed off the back foot to point
the extra bounce there, tried to push it hard off the back foot, made no contact as it rose past him
back of a length just outside off, hit straight to extra cover
back of a length outside off, went after it again, too quick for him there, was too late on the shot
banged in hard on middle, gets back and knocks it down back on the pitch
bowled full on the off, defended to cover off the front foot
bowled down the leg side, called a wide
class from Sidebottom, bowled full on middle, presents the full face and drives it stylishly down the ground wide of mid-on for a boundary
short of a good length outside off, pushed to cover off the back foot
angling it in towards the off stump, pushed to cover, bowled on a good length this time
worked away off the front foot wide of midwicket for a single
short of a good length outside off, holds its line and Anderson lets it through
tossed up, bowled on a good length outside off, pushed to cover
threw it up on middle and leg, tried to work it through square leg, was struck on the pads
pushed through quicker outside off, Sidebottom tried to defend it but it zipped past him
turned in sharply from a good length outside off, Sidebottom tries to defend it off the back foot, it beats him through the gate and the keeper for four byes
tries to work it across the line, gets a leading edge well over extra cover for a single
pushed into the leg side wide of midwicket for one more
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the back foot to the bowler
full on middle, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
back of a length on the off, punched back to the bowler
shortish on middle, presents the straight bat back to Franklin

worked off the back foot to midwicket, Sidebottom yells NO but Anderson is already halfway down the pitch, a direct hit at the bowler's end attempted but it misses by a fair distance, overthrows result in one more to the total
banged in short outside off, is surprised by the extra bounce and makes way
Vettori finishes it off, bowled on a good length on middle, rose up to Sidebottom who gets forward and just chips it straight to midwicket

inn2.comm: on target, short of a good length on the off, rocks back and defends it hard down towards cover
bowled full on the off, pushed through a diving extra cover, wide of mid-off, for a single to get off the mark
beaten, in the channel outside off, touch fuller, prodding at it is Guptill from the crease, it moves away just a hint to beat the outside edge
short of a good length outside off and nips away, a little wider from the previous one and Guptill watches it through
beaten, wonderfully bowled, bowled from wide of the crease, angling in towards off and getting it to move away after pitching, Guptill pushes through the line and is beaten
bowled on a good length on the off, tries to driven through, the movement off the pitch has him in trouble again, gets a thick outside edge behind point for three runs
four to the total, swinging in and sliding down the leg side, clips his pads to beat the diving keeper to the boundary
inward movement again, bowled on a good length on middle, turned away to midwicket
moving in, pushed it wide of the batsman and there was enough width there for him to leave it alone
short of middle and leg, turned away off his hips through square leg for a couple of runs
short of a good length on middle and leg, too straight, turned down to fine leg for a single

appeal for lbw, darting back in from a good length outside off, McCullum was caught walking as he tried to work it through the leg side, flicked his pads on the way to the keeper, did it do too much, was it too high? We need a replay to confirm
lucky for Guptill, short of a length outside off, goes for the cut, gets a thick under edge wide of a diving keeper to the boundary
tempting line outside off, full and wide and swings away, left alone
gets a thick outside edge as he drives forward and it goes down to third man for a single
a touch too wide there, moving away from well wide of the off stump, left alone
shaping inwards this time, wide of the crease, shouldered arms to that one
bowled full and wide, driven hard, flies down off the outside edge to third man for a single
fullish on middle, worked away through the leg side field for a couple of runs

appeal for lbw, came back in from a good length on the off stump, tried to drive it past midwicket, missed and was struck on the back pad, replays show it would have clipped the bails, close shout there
beautifully picked, bowled full outside off, thwacked hard over midwicket for a couple of bounces over the ropes
full and wide, goes for a booming drive but can't reach it
beaten by the extra bounce, short of a good length outside off, came back in to beat the outside edge as he tried to defend it off the back foot
beaten! Angling in and then shooting away, Guptill goes back to defend but the ball's too good for him
pitched it up on the off and got it to move away, Guptill drove through the line and was beaten by the movement
Guptill surviving dangerously here, bowled on a good length on the off, just pushes through with limited foot movement, thick outside edge through the point region all the way to the ropes
just wide of Anderson, bowled full on the off, just drove through, a chip past the outstretched hands of the bowler through mid-off for three more, all these count, New Zealand are off briskly here
short and wide, slashes hard, gets a thick edge that flies over the slips wide of third man for a boundary
back of a length on the off, pushed into the off side on the back foot
driving length outside off, left alone through to the keeper
short of a good length outside off, just lets it through to the keeper
back of a length outside off, a hint of inward movement there, left alone
nipped back in sharply, dropped into the leg side in front of square leg for a quick single
goes after it, just a fraction short outside off, moves across and pulls it over square leg , didn't time it as well as he intended to, three more, they're eating into the deficit now
darts back in from a good length on middle, tries to force it past midwicket, struck high on the pads
pushed off the back foot wide of extra cover for a single
back of a length a touch too wide outside off, left alone to the keeper
nice, juicy half-volley for Guptill, enough width as well, he crashes it through mid-off for a boundary, easily done, nice flourish too
short of a good length on the off, moves away to beat the outside edge for the umpteenth time
back of a length on the off, pushed towards cover
bowled on a good length outside off, gets forward and taps it towards point
Sidebottom sees him charge down the track and hurls it wide, but McCullum has it covered, reaching for it and slicing it miles over the deep-point boundary
appeal for caught-behind, made room again and the bowler chased him, went for it, trying to swing it over midwicket, clipped the pad flap on the way to the keeper
shuffles across to try to flick it fine, it pitched outside leg, moved in and struck him on the pads
wild swing again from McCullum, short and wide, tries to murder it through square leg but makes no contact
smashed it, he's in a hurry to finish this off, short of a length outside off, charges down the track and creams that through point for another boundary
goes for the scoop, bowled on a good length on middle, shuffles, bends low and tries to paddle it over the short-fine fielder, makes no contact and it goes over the stumps through to the keeper
a slap, short and wide, Guptill gets into the act, swats it like one does while killing a fly, well wide of of mid-off for four
back of a length outside off, lets it through to the keeper
bowled full outside off, doesn't go for the drive, lets it go
there's that extra bounce, short outside off, Guptill thought of playing the cut, but it rose up to a level that he didn';t want to reach
back of a length outside off, tried the cut again but wasn't able to connect
slips it wide of the off stump again and Guptill leaves it to McCullum to do all the smashing, leaves it be
bowled full on middle, drilled hard but straight to mid-off, he's middling them nicely
short and wide, makes room to caress that over point, the shot was on but he had made too much room, didn't reach it
pushed it fuller, came down the track to drive that through mid-off, it moved away to beat the outside edge and the stumps
bowled short at 140.7 kmph, chopped down to cover after making way
that's disappeared, short and wide, had made room and upper-cut it high and handsome over third man for a six

in the air and safe, bowled full on the off, came down the track and tried to loft it into the stands over his head but mistimed it, got more elevation than distance but it cleared the in-field comfortably, three more to keep the strike
short and wide, McCullum's eyes lit up, went for a ferocious cut but didn't connect
was targeting the stands again, short outside off, went for the pull but as he's done quite a few times this innings, missed
hurled it short, rocks back and pulls it wide of short fine leg for four more, rolled his wrists over it nicely
McCullum defends! Nice length, just short of a good length on the off, held its line there, defended off the back foot to the bowler
bowled on a length on middle, made room to smash that down the ground but mistimed it, just a single wide of mid-on
Guptill goes after it, bowled full outside off, drives it uppishly wide of the diving extra cover to beat mid-off to the ropes
short of a good length on the off, guided down to point off the back foot
bowled on a good length on middle, makes room and pushes it wide of extra cover for a single
beaten, shaping in towards the off stump and gets it to nip away after pitching, Guptill was almost done in there, clueless
beaten again! Bowled on a good length on middle, came down the track and tried to close the face, it moved away to beat the outside edge and just whisked past the off stump
some late movement there, counters it by guiding it wide of point for a quick single
slower offcutter, bowled at 99.5kmph, turned wide of short fine for a single
banged in short, poor ball that, he's been harsh on those and continues to be so, went for a fierce pull, got the top edge that took it well over the fine-leg boundary
length ball outside off, mistimes a drive to mid-off
that's gone! Made room and Broad pushed it wide, tried to thump that over the covers, mistimed it completely and it landed safely in the palms of Bopara at cover
short of a good length on middle, gets back and defends it to mid-on
Guptill's unflustered, he continues his merry way, full and wide from Broad and Guptill square-drives it through point and cover for a boundary
short and wide, shapes up for a square cut but doesn't connect
bowled on a good length on middle, rocks back and defends it wide of the bowler

chance of a run out, full on middle, pushed wide of Bopara at midwicket, Guptill is halfway down the pitch when Broom refuses the run, good throw to the bowler's end but Collingwood is unable to get back in time and collect, takes off the bails with his hand instead
short of a length, runs it down to third man for a single
shuffles well across, risky but he picked it well, driving it down towards deep midwicket for a couple
full outside off, driven down the ground to long-off for a single
beaten, bowled at 123.4 kmph, landing on a good length on the off and shoots away to miss the outside edge as he plays forward, seen it plenty of times today
bowled it full on the off, just chipped it, fell well short of mid-off
smacked that hard but straight to the fielder, short outside off, pulled down to deep midwicket
risky leave that, came back in sharply and went over the off stump as he let it go
angling in towards middle and off, pushed it back firmly to the bowler
slightly short outside off, tapped down towards point off the front foot
short of a length, pushes it down towards extra cover
rose up from a good length outside off, plays away from his body slightly as he taps it down to cover
short and wide, goes for the cut but is unable to connect
moves across, closes the face and works it through midwicket for a single
banged in short on middle, mistimes a pull towards deep square leg
shot! Free swing of the arms, bowled on a length, walked down the track and whacked it into the stands over long-on, good clean strike, also brings up the 100
Harper gives it a wide, full outside off, wasn't that wide, a harsh call there
short of a good length outside off, punched to mid-off
short and wide, cut hard wide of third man, Sidebottom dives to his right to cut that off but can't prevent them from taking two
bowling it full on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
angling it on leg stump, tries to drive it past midwicket, is struck on the pads, would have been sliding down, needless throw at the striker's end, concedes an overthrow
lands on a good length outside off, moves away, left alone
nips back in to rap him on the pads, they sneak a leg bye as rolls down wide of point
banged in short on middle, didn't pick it, was hit hard on the chest as he tried to fend it away
a bunt, reaches his half-century with a slap over the bowler's head, short again from Broad, poor length and he gets the treatment
short of a good length outside off, left alone to the keeper
bowled full on middle, worked away down to fine leg for a single
the legcutter, bowled at 137.3 kmph, tries to cut it past point, doesn't connect
banged in short outside off, tries to poke at it but misses yet again
the bouncer, bowled at 140.5 kmph, Broom backs away from it
targeting middle and leg, dropped into the leg side for a single
the legcutter beats him again, trying desperately for a single down to third man, played away from his body there, missed it

run-out chance , on middle and leg, dropped into the leg side in front of the bowler, Anderson runs forward and collides with Guptill, turns and tries to throw down the stumps at the non-striker's end but misses, would have been out had that hit
the legcutter does the trick, pitching it on middle and off, Guptill pushes at it as it moves away, gets a thick edge to Swann at first slip who pouches it comfortably moving to his left
short of a good length on the off, defended down towards point off the back foot
takes the bottom-hand off at the right time there, shot off the pitch but he countered it well by playing it with gently down to third man for a single

what a catch! England are fighting back, albeit a little too late, short of a good length outside off, moved away just a hint as he tried to defend off the back foot, got a thick edge and Swann, at second slip, dived full length to his right to take that with one hand inches from the ground
beaten, back of a length just outside off, bowled at 141 kmph, moved away as he tried to block that off the back foot
just kept a touch low, the first of the innings, he was expecting it to bounce more than that but it whizzed past the bat
slightly short outside off, defended off the back foot to point
oooh, the short one had him in trouble, just stood back and played at it, it struck high on the bat and lobbed up well wide of slip, a single to third man
short of a good length outside off, pushed to point
bowled short on middle, shuffles across and works it down to fine leg
pushed away in front of mid-on for a quick single
short on the off stump, walks across to defend it towards point
walks across and tickles it down to fine leg for a single
bowled on a good length on middle and leg, Broom taps that into the off side very unconvincingly
fullish on the off, defended back to the bowler
banged in short outside off, moves away and he backs away from it
short on middle, holds its line, bowled at 143.2 kmph, gets on he back foot and drops it down on the pitch
short, a legcutter, that, well outside off, the batsman shoulders arms
edged and gone! He's walked off, the short one does the trick, banged in hard on the off stump, it kicks off, moves away and catches the glove on the way to the keeper
bowled on a good length outside off and it just took off, well wide so he could let it go without any difficulty
already in a bit of trouble, hard and short on middle, shuffles, it catches him high on the bat, and it lobs up but lands safe between short square leg and short fine
a pressure-relieving boundary, short and wide, Broom chases in, cutting it hard and wide of the fielder and point for four
nips back in from a good length outside off, defended back to the bowler
darting it in towards middle, just punches it through midwicket for a couple and there's an overthrow from the deep which concedes another run, three more
short of a good length outside off, holds its line, lets it through to the keeper
short on middle, rocks back, closes the face and pushes it in front of deep square leg for a single
too straight, angling in on middle, worked away to deep square leg for a single
short on middle, plays at it a little hard and it drops just in front of Bopara at short square leg
back of a length on the off, moves back and punches it to midwicket
short outside off, run down to third man for a single
walks across and turns it down to fine leg for one more
raps him on the glove with that short one from wide of the crease, gets it wide of point for a single down to third man

one more! Hopkins goes, Broad gets his fourth. Bowled from wide of the crease, hurls it short just outside off, Hopkins is pushed back as he tried to keep it down, it flicks the glove and goes through to the keeper
short down the leg side, concedes a free run
short of a good length outside off, comes back in, is beaten as he tries to dab it to cover
short outside off, chops it down to third man for a single
short of a good length outside off, rocks back and drops it in front of cover
walks across, Sidebottom aims at middle and off, pushes it back to the bowler
short and wide, attempts a risky shot, tries to upper cut it over the slips, misses
important runs these, short and wide, reaches for it and cuts it over point for a welcome boundary
short on the off stump, gets back, turns the face and plays it down towards midwicket
a bouncer gone bad, too short this time, above head height, well above, called a wide
worked away off the back foot to short square leg on the bounce
shortish on leg stump, tries to work it fine, struck on the thigh pad, sneaks a leg bye
short on middle, makes way and jabs it down towards backward point
bowled on a good length on middle, pushed back to the bowler
New Zealand are through to the semi-finals, short on leg stump, worked away through square leg for a couple
one more down! Poor shot from Broom there, short and wide, tried to nudge it down to third man, it came back in just a hint to take the outside edge straight to Morgan
bowled on a good length outside off, pushed through to point
a run gifted, hurls a wide down the leg side
kept low, a rare one this innings, short of a good length outside off and just rolled through
back of a length outside off, chops it down to point
angling it in towards middle, pushes it back down the ground through mid-on for a couple of runs

dropped, Bopara spills it at short square leg, bowled short on leg stump, Vettori just works it off the back foot, a low chance but he could have taken it, would have added an interesting twist to the game
all over, short on middle, pulls it away over midwicket to seal victory and top the group
